candidates.title: SHAO, EDA2 receiver types, plus MacOS 14 Arm64 release and tests
Use pyo3 to provide a direct python interface.
candidates.body:
This is not ready to be merged!

This commit contains code that *could* allow `pymwalib` to be deprecated. Work to do and considerations:

- The Python module name becomes `mwalib` and can't be `pymwalib` (it needs to match the name of the Cargo package)
- I've copied `pymwalib` examples over, but they currently don't work because (1) imports need to be updated and (2) there are other differences
  - The `check_mwalib_version` function shouldn't be needed anymore; no libmwalib.so file is needed to run the pyo3 Python code.
  - Installation instructions should be added
    - (I usually just use `maturin develop --release -b pyo3 --features=python --strip`)
- `maturin` (the Python tool used to install the Rust code as a Python package) likes you to have a pyproject.toml file (or something like this); this should be added.
- Performance should be checked. Maybe it's worse?
- `CorrelatorContext` should be good to go, but I haven't put in any work for `VoltageContext`
- Add function signatures for nice help texts in Python
- Provide CI-pre-built wheels for compatible python versions (3.7+)?
  - Examples to do this exist in hyperbeam

So, there's a lot of stuff to be done, **but**, it should mean less work long term because `pymwalib` needs to be kept in sync with `mwalib`.

candidates.title: Errors and speed ups
candidates.body: Comments are in the commits. Please ask me if there are questions. No breaking changes, all pretty straight forward. If all's good, let me know and I'll bump and merge.
